1. e4 ({After having created multiple Chessable courses covering} 1. e4 {with White and various Black defenses against it, I'm thrilled to explore yet another fascinating battleground – the Modern Defense. My first Chessable course against 1.e4 focused on the solid 1...e5 and the Archangel, but this time, we're stepping into a more offbeat and dynamic territory.}) ({No discussion of} 1. e4 {feels complete without the classic 'Best by Test' label! If we were to take a poll between 1.e4 , 1.d4 , 1.c4 , and 1.Nf3 , I believe 1.e4 would still come out on top. To reinforce this, here’s an interesting tidbit: when Magnus Carlsen was once asked in a press conference which first move he would choose if he had to play it for the rest of his life, his answer was clear and confident: 1.e4 .}) ({With that in mind, let's dive into this course, embrace the Modern Defense, and take on the challenge of leading a new battle against} 1. e4 $1) 1... g6 {Welcome to Mastering the Modern Defense: 1.e4 g6! Greetings, ambitious players and chess lovers. : (In this course, we will dive deep into the Modern Defense 1.e4 g6 , an incredibly flexible and dynamic opening that allows Black to dictate the pace of the game. Unlike rigid setups where Black follows classical development patterns, the Modern is all about adaptability, provoking White to overextend while we stay solid and strike back at the right moment. The core philosophy of this repertoire is simple – invite White to take the center, then dismantle it with precise, resourceful counterplay. Whether it's hypermodern pawn structures, fluid piece maneuvers, or deep positional ideas, this course will equip you with everything you need to play the Modern Defense with confidence. The lines I've selected are based on practical strength and deep engine-backed analysis. You'll find rich middlegame plans, unexpected tactical shots, and the kind of fighting positions where creativity shines. We will cover all critical continuations White can throw at us, from direct pawn storms to solid positional setups, ensuring you are well-prepared against any opponent. The Modern is not just an opening – it's an entire philosophy of chess. It challenges conventional wisdom and forces both players into an unbalanced fight from the very start. If you enjoy outplaying opponents in fresh, unconventional positions while keeping maximum flexibility, this course is for you! Let's get started and master the art of the Modern Defense!)} *

