1. e4 g6 2. Bc4 Bg7 3. Qf3 {[%csl Rf7] Threatening mate in one on [f7].} e6 {[%cal Gg8e7,Gd7d5] Of course, not falling into the childish trap of mate in one. One more point to add is that now the combination of the bishop on [c4] and the queen on [f3] falls flat.} 4. Ne2 {[%cal Gd2d4]} c5 {[%csl Rd4] Not allowing White to conquer the center with [d4].} 5. d3 Nc6 6. Nbc3 Nge7 {[%csl Rf3][%cal Gd7d6,Ge8g8] This is the right setup for Black. Next, we will play ...[d6], castle, and so on. The queen on [f3] is misplaced, which gives Black a preferable position.} 7. h4 h6 $15 (7... h6 {With the intention to meet} 8. h5 {with} g5 {and also not allowing the [Bg5] pin, which is possible in the case of 7...h5 .}) *

