e point of it as Black is planning ...[Bf5] to pressurize the [e4]-knight.} ({Nothing wrong with the natural} 7... Qb6 {either.}) 8. Be2 Bf5 {[%csl Re4]} 9. Nf3 ({If} 9. Ng3 {, we can just ignore it and play} Nd7 {since after} 10. Nxf5 gxf5 $1 {followed by ...[O-O-O], Black's position is already preferable. White will struggle to finish development.}) 9... Nd7 $10 {[%csl Re4][%cal Ge8c8]} ({We cannot grab the pawn immediately by} 9... Bxe4 10. dxe4 Qxe4 {due to the strong} 11. Rh4 Qf5 12. Bxh6 Bxh6 13. Qd4 {and White creates a ruckus in Black's camp. With the text move, we are planning for long castle, and the pressure on the [e4]-knight is always there.}) *

