 always keep an eye on the [b8]-[h2] diagonal.} 9. c3 O-O 10. O-O Rad8 {[%csl Rh4][%cal Gd7g4,Gf6g4]} (10... Ng4 {is equally possible, but before that, we can bring our rooks into play. Black has full compensation here with ...[Bg4] and ...[Ng4] ideas floating in the air. White's [h4]-pawn is a clear weakness, and that adds up as well.}) *

