1. e4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 3. h4 {Trying to unsettle Black early. But not being properly equipped without developing the pieces first is not effective. Let's see how to respond to this system of a premature [h4] push.} d5 $1 {The principles of chess are still in good use – flank attack met by central strike. Like in the other variations we have seen in this chapter, we continue in the same spirit by hitting the center.} 4. e5 (4. exd5 Qxd5 5. Nf3 Bg4 {and Black is doing well. The weakness created by pushing the pawn to [h4] will begin to tell.}) 4... c5 {[%csl Rd4]} 5. c3 {Fortifying the pawn on [c3] to keep the [d4]-[e5] pawn chain intact.} h5 {[%csl Rh4] Now it's time to stop the h-pawn. The black knight on [g8] will head to [h6].} 6. Nf3 Nc6 7. Bb5 Bg4 $15 {[%csl Rd4][%cal Gg4d1,Gg8h6,Ge8g8,Gd8b6] Black has nicely secured the bishop without having to worry about [h2]-[h3].} *

