are not critical.}) 15... Qb4 {[%csl Rb2][%cal Gb4b2]} (15... Bxc3+ 16. bxc3 Qxc3+ {is worse for Black after} 17. Kf2 {and the absence of the dark-squared bishop will simply ruin our king.}) 16. Qb5 Be6 17. Kf2 ({After} 17. O-O {, we can take on [c3]:} Bxc3 18. bxc3 Qxc3 {and White's bishop on [e3] is under attack. With the knight jumping to [d4], Black neutralizes the absence of the dark-squared bishop.}) 17... Rfd8 {Exchanging on [b4] will only activate Black's pieces, so unless White is forced to, they will not exchange on [b4].} 18. Rad1 Qxb5 19. Bxb5 Nb4 {[%csl Ra2][%cal Gb4a2,Gg7b2,Ge6a2] Bringing more forces.} 20. a4 ({If} 20. a3 {, then} Nc2 {is incoming.}) 20... a6 21. Be2 Bb3 22. Rxd8+ Rxd8 23. Rc1 Nd3+ 24. Bxd3 Rxd3 {[%cal Gg7b2] Right now, Black is threatening ...[Bxc3] to enter into an opposite-colored bishop ending. And if White scoots away with the knight, then ...[Bxb2] is there.} *

