n, but Black has to be ready to defend a passive position after, for example,} 16. Bh3 Ng8 17. e5 Nxf6 18. exf6+ Kg8 19. Rd5 Bxd7 20. Rhd1 a5 21. Bxd7 Nh7 22. Bh3 Rxd5 23. Rxd5 Nxf6 24. Rb5 b6 25. c5 Rb8 {.}) 16. Bh3 Ng5 {[%csl Rh3]} 17. Bg2 Ne6 {[%csl Rd7][%cal Gc6d4]} 18. Rd5 Nb4 $132 {[%cal Gb4d5,Gb4a2] White drops the [a2]-pawn, which balances the material.} *

