1. e4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 3. Nf3 {White starts with [Nf3] and intends to complete development on the kingside first, delaying [Nc3].} d6 4. Bc4 {[%cal Gc4g8] Bobby Fischer's favorite place for the bishop. If you notice, in his games, he liked to place the bishop on [c4] in the majority of cases.} Nf6 {[%csl Re4]} 5. e5 {This is premature here, as White is unable to take back with the pawn.} dxe5 6. Nxe5 {[%csl Rf7]} O-O 7. O-O Nfd7 {[%csl Re5] The [e5]-knight has to be removed.} 8. Qe2 (8. Nf3 c5 {leads to a comfortable game for Black.}) 8... Nb6 {[%csl Rc4,Rd4][%cal Gd8d4,Gb6c4] Now White is forced to lose the bishop pair.} 9. c3 {[%csl Gc3,Gd4]} Nxc4 10. Nxc4 b6 $10 {[%cal Gc8b7] I like Black here due to the simple fact of having the bishop pair.} *

