1. e4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 3. Nf3 {White starts with [Nf3] and intends to complete development on the kingside first, delaying [Nc3].} d6 4. Bd3 Nf6 5. O-O O-O 6. Re1 {White intends to complete development without including [h3] in the mix.} Nc6 {[%cal Ge7e5] This is our main setup, preparing the central confrontation with ...[e5].} 7. d5 (7. c3 e5 {will transpose to the main line arising from 4.c3 . The text move is the only independent line.}) 7... Nb4 {[%csl Rd3]} 8. Bf1 {[%csl Ge1,Ge4] Now we can see the point behind the quick [Re1].} e6 {Undermining the advanced central pawn is necessary to free up some space for our pieces.} 9. c3 Na6 10. dxe6 Bxe6 $10 {[%cal Gf8e8] And next, we can place our rook on [e8] with a fine game. All our pieces have completed their development, and there is no weakness in our position.} *

