e game.} Nfd7 9. Bf4 {[%csl Ge5,Gf4] This happened in the game Esipenko-Liang, World Blitz 2024. White supports the pawn on [e5].} Bb7 $1 (9... Nc6 {seems to hit the mark, targeting the [e5]-pawn – one of our main objectives. However, White has a surprisingly powerful idea with} 10. Qc1 {, intending [Rd1], which leaves us unable to capture the [e5]-pawn.}) 10. Qd2 (10. e6 fxe6 11. Ng5 {is nothing to be scared of, as we have} Rf6 {.}) 10... Nc6 {[%csl Re5] And now we bring our knight.} 11. Rad1 dxe5 12. dxe5 Ncxe5 13. Nxe5 Nxe5 14. Qe3 Nd7 $10 {[%cal Rd1d8] Black is totally fine. White is a pawn down but has compensation, thanks to the pressure along the d-file.} *

