h sides.} 8. Be3 {One of the logical moves in this position.} e5 {[%csl Rd4] Time to challenge the center.} 9. d5 Ne7 {We get to some kind of King's Indian without the white pawn on [c4].} 10. a5 {It looks good to gain more space, but there is a drawback.} Ng4 11. Bd2 f5 {[%csl Re4] Black gets the desired breakthrough in.} 12. Ng5 Nf6 13. f3 h6 14. Ne6 Bxe6 15. dxe6 d5 $10 {[%csl Re6] Black's position is preferable due to White's lonely pawn on [e6].} *

