1. e4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 3. Nc3 {[%csl Rd5] A logical developing move, gaining control over the [d5]-square. Next, White will decide where to place the other pieces.} d6 4. Nge2 ({This is a better move order to reach the fianchetto setup, as} 4. g3 {gives a lot of options for Black.}) 4... Nf6 {Black aims for castle and a quick ...[e5].} 5. g3 O-O 6. Bg2 e5 7. O-O exd4 $1 8. Nxd4 Nc6 (8... Nc6 {And now White cannot hold the d4-knight there by} 9. Be3 {due to the} Ng4 {jump. So, White is forced to exchange or retreat, which is why I added an exclaim to Black's 7th move.}) 9. Nde2 Rb8 $1 {[%cal Gb7b5] Preparing to expand with ...[b5].} 10. a4 Re8 {[%csl Re4]} (10... b6 {immediately would unnecessarily hand White the} 11. Nd5 {jump. The text move prevents that.}) 11. h3 b6 $10 {[%csl Re4][%cal Gc8b7,Gc6b4] Followed by ...[Bb7] and ...[Nb4] and Black is comfortable.} *

