1. e4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 3. Nc3 {[%csl Rd5] A logical developing move, gaining control over the [d5]-square. Next, White will decide where to place the other pieces.} d6 4. Be2 {[%cal Gh2h4,Gh4h5] White delays the [g1]-knight development for ideas like [h4]-[h5] or [Be3] and [Qd2] without having to worry about ...[Ng4] jumps.} Nf6 (4... a6 {is also possible, but I would like to not stick with one plan of ...[b5]; hence, I prefer development first so that we can adapt according to what the position needs, like ...[e5] or ...[c5] breaks, and so on.}) 5. Nf3 O-O {We have transposed to another chapter.} *

