e the position in a comfortable manner.} 9. dxc5 Nxc5 10. Bxc5 dxc5 11. e5 {[%csl Rg7] Blunting the [g7]-bishop looks logical.} Qb6 {[%cal Gc5c4,Gb6g1] Threatening the ...[c4] discovered check.} 12. Be4 Bxe4 13. Nxe4 Nh6 $10 {[%cal Ge8g8] Followed by castle – the knight on [h6] will be brought into the game via [f5], and Black can always activate the [g7]-bishop by ...[f6] at the right moment.} *

