e d-file will be under the rook's control on [d1].} 9. dxc5 Nxc5 {[%csl Rc3,Gc5,Rd3,Gg7] Black's pieces have been activated, and now White's bishop on [d3] and the knight on [c3] are under pressure.} 10. O-O-O Nxd3+ 11. Rxd3 Bxc3 12. Rxc3 Nf6 {[%csl Re4]} (12... Bxe4 {fails to} 13. Bd4 {.}) 13. e5 Nd5 {[%csl Gb7,Gd5] This knight on [d5] is really powerful, blocking White's play on the d-file.} 14. Rd3 dxe5 15. fxe5 Qc8 $10 {[%cal Gd5e3,Gc8c4] Scooting away from the pin on the d-file. Black is comfortable here.} *

