e same time.} Nh6 {[%csl Rf5][%cal Ge8g8,Gh6f5,Gc7c5]} (8... c5 {is recommended by Vjeko in his Uncompromising Modern Defense course. I like the text move of developing the knight first and then carrying the important break ...[c5], keeping the options flexible. Doing necessary things first, like developing the knight.}) 9. Qe2 {[%cal Ge1c1] The main move, planning to castle long.} c5 $1 {Time to strike before White castles long.} 10. e6 (10. O-O-O b4 {and the white knight has no proper square since} 11. Ne4 c4 {exists, and 11.Na4 Bc6 also keeps the knight under threat.}) 10... O-O $3 {11...fxe6 leads to unnecessary complications after 12.Ng5 and so on.} 11. exd7 Bxf3 12. Qxf3 cxd4 13. Be4 Rb8 $15 {Black regains the material investment with interest.} *

