e same time.} Nh6 {[%csl Rf5][%cal Ge8g8,Gh6f5,Gc7c5]} (8... c5 {is recommended by Vjeko in his Uncompromising Modern Defense course. I like the text move of developing the knight first and then carrying the important break ...[c5], keeping the options flexible. Doing necessary things first, like developing the knight.}) 9. Qe2 {[%cal Ge1c1] The main move, planning to castle long.} c5 $1 {Time to strike before White castles long.} 10. dxc5 (10. O-O-O b4 {and the white knight has no proper square since} 11. Ne4 c4 {exists, and 11.Na4 Bc6 also keeps the knight under threat.}) 10... dxe5 (10... Nxc5 11. Bxc5 dxc5 12. O-O-O {is the problem.}) 11. Nxe5 Nxe5 12. fxe5 O-O 13. O-O-O Qc7 {[%csl Re5][%cal Gc7e5]} (13... Bxe5 {is not possible due to} 14. Bxh6 {.}) 14. Bf4 Qxc5 15. h4 {[%cal Gh4h5]} Bc8 $1 {[%cal Gc8g4] Rerouting the bishop to counter with ...[Bg4] ideas, not allowing White to roll with [h5].} 16. Ne4 Qd5 {[%cal Gc8g4,Gd5a2]} (16... Qd5 {Thanks to the double threat of ...Qxa2 and ...Bg4, White is forced to repeat the position with} 17. Nc3 Qc5 {.}) *

