l Gd8c7] Giving some space for the queen on [c7].} 14. g4 Qc7 {[%cal Gc6c5] Now ...[c5] is on the cards, as the queen is no longer under the radar of [d1]-rook.} 15. Rh2 c5 16. Bb5+ Nfd7 17. Qg7 Rf8 18. c3 (18. Qxh7 {is met by} cxd4 19. Rxd4 Qc5 {winning.}) 18... d5 {[%cal Gc7h2,Gc5d4,Gc7c1] What a messy position!} 19. Rhd2 Nc4 $132 {[%csl Rd2]} (19... Nc4 {The position is super complex. One sample line might continue after} 20. exd5 Nxd2 21. Nxd2 bxc3 22. bxc3 Rb8 {and so on...}) *

