way to recapture. If} 11... Ndxe5 {, then} 12. Bf6 {is annoying.}) 12. O-O c6 13. Nc7 Nxf3+ 14. Qxf3 Qe5 (14... Qe5 {Thanks to this idea, Black saves the rook.} 15. Nxa8 $2 {is too greedy and loses after} Qxg5 {since White's knight is trapped either on [a8] or [c7].}) 15. Bf4 Qc5+ 16. Kh1 ({After} 16. Be3 Bd4 $1 17. Bxd4 Qxd4+ {followed by ...[Rb8], Black is fine again. Just to amuse ourselves, we'll have a quick look at two engine variations that end up in a draw, as always:} 18. Kh1 Rb8 19. e5 Qxe5 {(19...Nxe5 20.Qf6 Bxh3 21.gxh3 Qe3 22.Rae1 Qxh3+ with perpetual check. )} 20. Rae1 Qxc7 21. Re7 Ne5 22. Qf6 Nd7 23. Qf3 Ne5 {with a draw by repetition. This was for illustrative purposes only; Black has other options along the way.}) 16... Rb8 17. Qg3 Ne5 {The knight blocks the pressure along the [h2]-[b8] diagonal.} 18. Nd5 Re8 $10 {Securing the knight on [e5] and all is good.} *

