 in the exchange of queens.}) 10. Be4 Qxd1 11. Rxd1 Bf5 {[%csl Rc2,Re4] Removing the key piece.} 12. Bxf5 gxf5 {[%csl Rc2]} 13. Ne1 a5 {White was planning [a3] to kick the knight so we are making a square on [a6] for it after ...[a5].} 14. a3 Na6 {[%cal Ga6c5]} 15. Be3 e6 $10 {[%cal Gf7f6] And next ...[f6] is incoming with an equal game. Black has no problems once we exchange the [e5]-pawn, solving the problem of space and as well the Dragon bishop on [g7].} *

