e have to change the knight's route to a different square.}) 9. Be2 Bg4 {[%csl Rd4] Target locked: the [d4]-pawn.} 10. d5 ({Unable to bear the tension, White goes all in, which leads to some exchanges.} 10. Be3 {would transpose to 9.Be3 Bg4 10.Be2 .}) 10... Bxf3 11. gxf3 Nxe5 12. f4 Nd7 13. Bxh5 gxh5 14. Qxh5 {White has regained the pawn back, but the whole central mass has vanished, and it is a big relief for Black.} Kh8 {Securing the king.} 15. Be3 Nb6 (15... Nf6 {is dubious, as it blocks the bishop on [g7] from ...[Bxc3], and White can face it with} 16. Qf3 {followed by long castle with a good position.}) 16. O-O-O Qd6 $132 {[%cal Gg7c3,Gd6a3]} (16... Qd6 {Black is threatening ...Bxc3 followed by ...Qa3+. This position is balanced after} 17. Nb5 Qb4 18. Bd4 Rg8 {. Just not 18...Qxb5? since after 19.Bxg7+ Kxg7 20.Rhg1+ Kh8 21.Rd3 , it is game over for Black.}) *

