k on our king, but it's not that simple – we have defensive resources.} 12. Bd3 Qe8 {leads to the same story.}) 12... h6 {At this point, White has multiple ways to launch an offensive.} 13. Qd3 $1 {[%cal Gd3g6] A true trial for Black. The position appears highly dangerous, yet this is the essence of the Modern Defense – wild, double-edged play.} Qe8 {[%cal Ge8g6] True to its role, the queen comes to the rescue, shielding her majesty. :} 14. Rxh5 {Black has just one move to stay in the game.} Nc6 $1 {[%csl Rd3][%cal Gc6b4] With the idea of jumping to [b4], aiming to deflect the queen from [d3].} 15. Rh4 {White is forced to relocate the rook, as ...[Nb4] would otherwise win it.} hxg5 16. Bxg5 Rf5 {[%csl Rg5][%cal Gf5g5]} 17. Qg3 Rxg5 $1 18. Qxg5 Bf6 {[%csl Ge8,Gg6] Thanks to our queen protecting the [g6]-pawn, we are able to carry out this operation.} 19. Qg3 Bxh4 20. Qxh4 Qf7 21. O-O-O Bb7 $10 {[%cal Ga8f8] Next on cards is ...[Rf8] followed by ...[Qf4]+, and Black can breathe a sigh of relief.} *

