ains stable and cannot be easily challenged. Additionally, the knight plays a crucial role in defending the [h6]-pawn, ensuring that Black can safely castle and complete development.} 9. Kb1 O-O {Finally!} 10. Qe1 {[%cal Gd1d8]} b5 $132 {[%cal Ga8b8,Gb5b4] Followed by ...[Rb8] and ...[b4], when Black generates counterplay on the queenside.} *

