y target the [g4]-knight.}) 9. a3 {[%csl Rb4]} e6 $1 {Now comes a Hippopotamus-like move, maintaining a solid and flexible setup, ensuring that White cannot easily break through with [d5] or [e5] to invade our territory.} 10. O-O Bb7 {[%cal Rb7h1]} 11. Rfe1 Ne7 {[%csl Re4] This is quite a solid setup for Black. Let's see a sample line to uncover some of Black's incredible ideas!} 12. Bd3 Nh5 {[%csl Rf4]} 13. Bh2 g5 $1 {Bazooka!} 14. hxg5 hxg5 15. Qxg5 Kd7 $132 {[%cal Ge7g6,Gd8g8] Wow! The pawn structure stands firm like a fortress, giving Black complete flexibility in maneuvering the king. With no immediate threats, we can freely redirect our forces towards the kingside and unleash chaos. Some ideas include ...[Ng6], ...[Qg8], and more, setting the stage for a powerful assault.} *

