{Find the best plan for Black.} 6... a6 $15 {[%cal Gb8c6]} ({After} 6... a6 {, Black prepares to play ...[Nc6] without worrying about the annoying [Bb5]+ pin, which would limit the flexibility of the knight. By playing ...[a6] first, Black ensures that White cannot pin the knight on [c6], allowing for easier development and a solid position. Once ...[Nc6] is played, Black can continue developing harmoniously with ...[e6] to solidify the center, followed by ...[Nge7] to prepare for further piece maneuvering. The move ...[h5] expands on the kingside, preparing ...[h4] to gain space and prevent White from easily launching a kingside attack. Finally, ...[Bg7] completes the fianchetto.}) *

