{Find the best plan for Black.} 14... Ne8 $1 {Since there is no ....[Ne4]-[d6], we go for ...[Ne8]-[d6].} 15. Bxa6 Nd6 16. Ne5 {White cannot retreat the bishop due to the hanging pawn on [a5].} Re8 $1 {[%csl Ge2][%cal Ge8e2,Ge7e6] The knight on [e5] is powerful, so we must address it. The text move prepares ...[e6], opening up the e-file and allowing Black to exert pressure on the strong knight on [e5]. By challenging the knight and utilizing the e-file, Black can neutralize White's central outpost and create further tactical or positional opportunities.} 17. b3 e6 18. dxe6 Rxe6 19. Bb2 Qc7 {[%cal Ga8e8]} 20. Rfd1 (20. Rfd1 {With the idea to meet} Ree8 {by} 21. Rd5 {.}) 20... Nxe5 21. fxe5 Nf5 {[%csl Re5][%cal Ge6a6,Ga8a6]} 22. Bc4 Rxe5 {The dust has settled. Black conquers the dark squares and has sufficient compensation.} *

