{Black is a pawn down. How to proceed?} 15... Ne8 $1 {[%cal Ge8d6,Gd6c4,Gg7b2]} ({This is another knight sortie to come to c4 via d6.} 15... Nd7 {is slow here, and White can react with} 16. f4 {, shutting the knight.}) 16. O-O-O (16. f4 Nb4 $1 (16... Nd6 {is imprecise due to} 17. e5 Nc4 18. Bc5) 17. e5 Nxd3+ 18. cxd3 Bg4 {∞ and the lights squares are in Black's control. Next, we can bring the [e8]-knight to the game via [c7].}) 16... Nd6 17. Rhe1 Nc4 {[%csl Gc4,Gg7][%cal Gg7b2,Gc4b2] Black creates counterplay with the [c4]-knight and [g7]-bishop combined.} *

