{Find the best plan for Black to create play on the queenside.} 9... Nfd7 $1 {[%cal Gc7c5] A very unusual idea, I must say. The plan revolves around the obvious ...[c5], which not only challenges White's center but also keeps the [g7]-bishop open and active. This maneuver effectively prevents White from pushing [e5], as Black maintains flexibility and control. Additionally, the bishop on [d3] obstructs the queen on [d2], preventing White from playing [Bh6] to challenge Black's kingside. This creates a situation where the [d4]-pawn is unsupported, further weakening White's position.} 10. f4 {[%cal Gg1f3]} Bb7 11. Nf3 c5 12. dxc5 Nxc5 $132 {[%csl Gb6,Gb7,Gc5][%cal Gg7b2,Gb7h1] We have brought all of our pieces to perfect positions.} *

