{Black to play!} 8... a5 $1 ({The direct} 8... Nd7 {is also possible, targeting the [d4]-pawn as the white pieces are piled up on the d-file, which obstructs the queen's support over the [d4]-pawn. This forces White to respond with 10.Nb3 .}) ({However,} 8... a5 $1 {is even more clever. It prepares ...[Nd7], and now White cannot play [Nb3] due to the immediate threat of ...[a4].}) 9. Re1 (9. Bc2 Nh5 {or 9...Nd7 and White has to answer questions to the [d4]-pawn.}) 9... Nd7 {[%csl Rd4] White is forced to release the tension now.} 10. d5 Ne7 $132 {[%cal Gf7f5] Black has a better version of the King's Indian. The ...[f5] breakthrough is coming next.} *

