{How to continue?} 20... Nexd5 $1 {Changing the dynamics of the game by an unexpected shot. This is another typical sacrifice when our knights are lined up on [f6] and [e7], and moreover, it comes with a tempo attacking the queen on [c3].} 21. exd5 Nxd5 22. Qb3 Nxe3 23. fxe3 e4 {[%csl Ra1,Rf3] All our moves are in sync, and only thanks to White's piece placement, the whole idea of the ...[Nxd5] sacrifice works.} 24. Nd4 c5 {[%csl Rd4]} 25. bxc5 dxc5 {[%cal Gg7a1]} 26. Ra6 {[%cal Gb3f7,Gf7g6] Now a concrete line is awaiting for us. Fasten your seat belts!} cxd4 27. Qxf7 {[%csl Rg6]} Qg5 {[%csl Rg3,Gg6]} 28. Qxd7 Qxg3 29. Qxe8 Qxe3+ 30. Kh1 Qc1+ 31. Bd1 Qxd1+ 32. Kh2 {[%csl Rg6]} Qh5 (32... Qh5 {After} 33. Qxe4 Qe5+ 34. Qxe5 Bxe5+ 35. Kg1 d3 {, the air has finally cleared up, and we have built a fortress. This edgame is a draw. We also have the d-pawn with us.}) *

