{How to create counterplay?} 17... e4 $1 {[%cal Gg7a1] The best and only move that helps Black maintain the balance. The key idea is to open up the long diagonal for the bishop, making it difficult for White to develop the [c1]-bishop smoothly.} 18. Rb1 {[%csl Gb1,Gb2] In order to free the [c1]-bishop.} c6 $1 19. Bxc6 (19. Bb3 a5 {and White is not able to maintain the pawn on [e6].}) 19... Bxe6 $10 {[%cal Ge6a2,Gg7b2] The wide open bishops create counterplay.} *

