{Black to play!} 12... Nh5 $1 {[%cal Gf7f5] The best move. The knight is quite active there, compared to being on [e8], to facilitate ...[f5].} 13. Bxh5 (13. a5 bxa5 14. Rxa5 f5 15. f3 c6 {⇆ and now, it's complete chaos on the board! This is exactly the kind of dynamic, double-edged position we seek when playing the Modern or King's Indian.}) 13... gxh5 14. Qxh5 Ng6 {[%cal Gf7f5] Followed by ...[f5] and Black is going to roll on the kingside with the bishop pair.} *

