{Black to play.} 9... c5 $1 {[%cal Gg7b2]} 10. O-O (10. c4 Qd6 11. O-O cxd4 12. Nxd4 Nc6 {, and once again, Black is making use of the monster bishop on [g7].}) 10... cxd4 11. Nxd4 Nc6 {[%cal Gg7a1]} 12. Bf3 {[%cal Gf3a8]} Qa5 13. Nxc6 bxc6 14. c3 (14. Bxc6 Rb8 {and White cannot save the [b2]-pawn.}) 14... Rd8 {[%cal Gd8d1]} 15. Qc1 (15. Qc2 {will come under the radar of the light-squared bishop on [c8] after} Bf5 {.}) 15... Qc7 {[%cal Gc8e6] Followed by ...[Be6] and Black is doing fine.} *

