[PlyCount "86"]
[GameId "2159115901613258"]

{We will see one more game of Magnus where he navigates the complications effortlessly.} 1. e4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 3. Nc3 d6 4. Be3 a6 5. Qd2 b5 6. h4 Nf6 {[%cal Gf6h5]} 7. f3 h5 8. O-O-O b4 9. Nd5 (9. Nce2 {, we have analyzed this move in the theoretical part.}) 9... Nxd5 10. exd5 a5 $6 {Black wastes some time, and now White has got the momentum of creating some ideas on the kingside or bringing his pieces towards the [d5]-pawn.} (10... c6 $1 {activates the knight on [b8] by getting rid of the [d5]-pawn.}) 11. Re1 $6 (11. Ne2 {and White makes use of the opportunity to contain the [d5]-pawn with [Nf4].} Nd7 (11... c6 12. Nf4 {⩲}) 12. Bg5 Nb6 13. Nf4 {± .}) 11... c6 $1 {Finally!} 12. dxc6 Nxc6 13. Bb5 Bd7 14. Bg5 Ra7 $1 15. Nh3 (15. Bxc6 Bxc6 {connects the rook with the pawn.}) 15... a4 16. Nf4 b3 {Black is charging up with a ruthless attack!} 17. a3 bxc2 18. Nd5 Nxd4 {[%csl Rc1,Rd2][%cal Gd4b3]} 19. Bxe7 (19. Nxe7 Nb3+ 20. Kxc2 Qc7+ $1 21. Kd1 Nxd2 22. Nd5+ Be5 23. Nxc7+ Rxc7 24. f4 Nc4 25. Bxc4 Rxc4 26. fxe5 d5 {∓}) 19... Nb3+ 20. Kxc2 Qc8+ 21. Kd1 Bxb5 22. Bxd6+ $2 (22. Qg5 {is the best resistance:} Nc5 23. Nf6+ Bxf6 24. Bxf6+ Kd7 25. Bxh8 Qxh8 26. Re7+ Kc6 27. Rxa7 Qxb2 28. Qe3 Qb1+ 29. Kd2 Qxh1 30. Qe8+ Kd5 31. Qxb5 Qxg2+ {. A crazy line, and it does not end here. In a rapid game, it is not easy for White to calculate this far ahead.}) 22... Kd8 {Now it's all over for White.} 23. Be7+ Rxe7 24. Nxe7+ Nxd2 $19 25. Nxc8 Nc4 26. Na7 Bd7 27. Re4 Nxb2+ 28. Ke2 f5 29. Rb4 Bc3 30. Rb8+ Kc7 31. Rxh8 Bxh8 32. Rc1+ Kb7 33. Rc2 f4 34. Rd2 Be6 35. Rd8 Bc3 36. Rd6 Bc4+ 37. Kf2 Kxa7 38. Rxg6 Nd3+ 39. Kg1 Bb2 40. Rg5 Kb6 41. Rxh5 Bxa3 42. Rh8 Bc5+ 43. Kh2 a3 0-1

