{The Modern Defense became an integral part of my repertoire 5-6 years ago, and I still use it from time to time. I have had good success with it, winning some important games at crucial moments. The opening offers a rich mix of dynamic counterplay and hypermodern ideas. Even in games where I was objectively worse, I managed to muddy the waters and navigate the complexities well, as this opening always provides abundant counterplay. I primarily used it against lower-rated opponents when playing for a win, and this approach proved quite successful. Now, I would like to share some of my games in the Modern Defense, highlighting the key ideas and practical effectiveness of this fascinating opening.} 1. Z0 *

