1. e4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 3. Nf3 d6 4. Bc4 Nf6 {[%csl Re4]} 5. Qe2 O-O 6. O-O Bg4 7. h3 Bxf3 {The point of giving up this bishop is to exert pressure on the [d4]-pawn.} 8. Qxf3 Nc6 {[%csl Rd4]} 9. c3 e5 10. Rd1 Nd7 {[%cal Gg7a1] Adding more and more pressure and also paving the way for ...[f5] breakthroughs.} 11. Be3 Kh8 $1 {[%cal Gf7f5] Next, ...[f5] is unstoppable.} 12. Na3 $6 (12. Qg3 {is necessary to meet ...[f5] breaks with [f4].} f5 13. exf5 gxf5 14. dxe5 Ncxe5 (14... dxe5 15. f4 {and now one can see why [Qg3] is important.}) 15. Bb3 Ng6 16. f4 {and the game continues.}) 12... f5 13. exf5 gxf5 14. dxe5 (14. Nc2 Qe8 {⩱}) 14... f4 $1 {Perhaps White missed this intermediate move.} 15. Qe4 {Here, I missed a golden chance to increase the advantage.} (15. Bd4 Ncxe5 $1 (15... Ndxe5 16. Qh5 Rf6 17. Bd5) 16. Qxb7 (16. Qh5 Rf6 17. Bd5 c6) 16... Rb8 17. Qxa7 Ra8 18. Qb7 Rxa3 19. bxa3 Nxc4 {∓ .}) 15... Bxe5 {[%cal Gd8e7,Ge7h7]} (15... fxe3 $4 16. Bd3 {is the trick White had in mind, but 15...Qg5! 16.Bd3 Qh6 17.Bc1 Ncxe5 -+ .}) 16. Bd4 Qg5 {[%cal Gf4f3]} 17. Qf3 Qg7 $6 (17... Nf6 {, bringing more energy, is a better move.}) 18. Nc2 Ne7 19. Bf1 ({White could have taken} 19. Qxb7 {and coped with the threat of ...[f3] with [Ne3]:} f3 20. Ne3 {and White is fine in the resulting complications.}) 19... c6 (19... c5 $1 20. Bxe5 Nxe5 21. Qxb7 Rab8 {∓}) 20. Ne1 Ng6 21. Qe4 $6 ({Better is} 21. Bd3 {.}) 21... Nf6 {[%cal Gf6e4]} 22. Qd3 c5 23. Nf3 {White was just playing for small cheapos.} Rae8 24. Re1 Nd7 25. Bxe5 Ndxe5 26. Nxe5 Nxe5 27. Qd5 (27. Qxd6 Nf3+) 27... Rf6 28. Re4 Rg8 29. Rxe5 dxe5 30. Qxe5 {I did not play accurately to maintain the advantage. Some lethargic moves here and there, and I was dropping all my pluses.} b6 $6 (30... Qg5 $1 31. Qe7 Rh6 {∓}) 31. Rd1 Rf7 32. Qe4 Qf6 33. Qf3 Rd8 34. Re1 Rff8 35. Qb7 f3 36. g3 Rd2 37. Re4 (37. Qxa7 Rxb2) 37... Qf7 38. Re7 Qg6 39. Re3 Qf5 40. g4 $2 {A big blunder, and now Black gets a chance to enter on the kingside.} (40. Qxa7 {holds the game.}) 40... Qf6 41. Re7 $4 Qh4 $19 {[%csl Rf2][%cal Gh4h7]} 0-1

