{This game was crucial, as a win would secure me a bronze medal at the Asian Championship, thanks to my strong tiebreaks based on the number of wins with Black. I had an advantage in this regard, having already won multiple games earlier in the tournament.} 1. e4 d6 2. d4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. Nf3 a6 {[%cal Gb7b5] I had to rely on my favorite weapon, the Modern Defense, to create a fighting game.} 5. a4 Nf6 6. h3 O-O 7. Be3 b6 {[%cal Gc8b7,Gb7h1]} (7... Nc6 {is another alternative discussed extensively in the theoretical section.}) 8. Bc4 e6 {[%csl Ga6,Gb6,Gd6,Ge6,Gg6] Forming a Hippo setup.} 9. O-O (9. d5 Re8) 9... Bb7 10. d5 e5 {I wanted to keep the complexity, and this choice makes sense, as it offers some practical chances.} (10... exd5 {is the best way, and we have checked this option in the course:} 11. exd5 Re8 {.}) 11. Ne1 $6 (11. b4 $1 {White has to act quickly on the queenside.} Nbd7 12. a5 b5 13. Bb3 Nh5 (13... Rc8 14. Qd3) 14. Ne2 f5 15. c4 {and he is quicker on the queenside.}) 11... Qe8 {[%cal Gf6h5,Gf7f5]} 12. Nd3 (12. g4 $1 {A typical prophylactic move, preventing ...[f5], a thematic idea we have encountered in some games from the previous Model Games chapter;} Nbd7 13. f3 {⩲ .}) 12... Nh5 13. Qd2 {Slowly, White has drifted away with his suboptimal moves, and now Black takes over.} (13. g4 Nf4) 13... f5 {[%csl Re4]} 14. f3 Nd7 15. a5 b5 16. Bb3 Kh8 (16... Ndf6 {⩱}) 17. Ne2 $6 Ndf6 {[%csl Re4] White is already in trouble.} 18. Qb4 fxe4 19. fxe4 c5 (19... g5 {-+ is crushing with the queen heading on [g6].}) 20. dxc6 Qxc6 {[%csl Re4]} 21. Nc3 Ng3 22. Bd5 Nxd5 23. Rxf8+ Rxf8 24. exd5 Qd7 $15 25. Bf2 Nf5 $15 {[%csl Gb7,Gg7,Rd5] A stable plus with two bishops and a vulnerable white pawn on [d5].} 26. Qe4 Rc8 27. Rd1 Rc4 28. Qe2 Qc8 {[%cal Gc8c2]} ({Exerting pressure along the c-file.} 28... Kg8 {∓ or 28...h5 ∓ is also better for Black.}) 29. Ne1 Nd4 30. Bxd4 Rxd4 31. Rxd4 exd4 32. Na2 Bxd5 33. Nb4 Bb7 34. Qe7 Kg8 35. Ned3 Bf8 36. Qf6 Qe8 37. Qxd4 Qe2 38. Nf4 Qe1+ 39. Kh2 Qe5 (39... Bg7 40. Qxd6 (40. Qa7 Qe4) 40... Bf8 {-+}) 40. Qf2 Qxb2 41. Nfd3 Qc3 42. Qb6 Qc8 43. Nf4 Qc4 44. Nbd3 Qe4 45. Qd8 Qe7 46. Qb6 Qe4 47. Qd8 Kf7 48. Qd7+ Be7 49. h4 h6 50. Qh3 g5 51. hxg5 hxg5 52. Qh5+ Kg7 53. Qg4 Kf8 54. Ne6+ Ke8 55. Nc7+ Kd8 56. Ne6+ Kc8 57. Ndf4 Qh7+ 58. Kg1 Qh4 {A nice game! Thanks to this win, I went on to secure the bronze medal at the Asian Championship. Sweet memories! :} 0-1

